      '<p>Job Title: Senior User Interface Developer</p>\n<p>Salary: Competitive</p>\n<p>Based: \u202fBrandAlley, Telephone House, 69-77 Paul Street, London, EC2A 4NW (remote during Covid-19</p>\n<p>Experience: Expert User Interface Developer / Magento 1 &amp; 2 Developer</p>\n<p>Reporting to: CTO</p>\n<p>Who We Are</p>\n<p>Brand Alley UK Limited is the UK\u2019s largest online flash sale fashion retailer and is currently going through a period of exponential growth. With upwards of 5 million members, we sell top branded fashion and homeware products, process tens of thousands of orders per day and we are one of the most successful E-Commerce brands in the UK.</p>\n<p>Operating between London and Delhi, our team of developers and Magento specialists work on a wide range of projects for the BrandAlley Web platform. Its dynamic, diverse and an incredibly exciting time as BrandAlley migrates its front-end web platform into Magento 2 and moves its entire back office team into a custom built platform consisting of a PIM, warehousing, merchandising, customer service, and marketing modules. With this new architecture in place 2021 will see a backlog of new features developed for <a href="http://www.brandalley.co.uk">www.brandalley.co.uk</a> and our European site (<a href="http://www.brandalley.fr">www.brandalley.fr</a>) built and migrated onto its own Magento 2 instance and connected into the same back office systems as the UK site.</p>\n<p>Along with the launch of our IOS and Android Apps, 2021 can also see the further break-up of the Magento user interface layer into rich Progressive Web Apps making this a truly exciting opportunity.</p>\n<p>Job Description</p>\n<p>We are looking for an experienced User Interface Developer with proven experience of working with large scale web applications to join our team. This role will be perfect for an individual who has been developing Magento User Interfaces for a number of years, has a heightened passion for making Magento work beyond its limits, creating high performance JavaScript, CSS and HTML and either is working with PWA technology right now or has at least begun the journey and is investing time in learning the technology.</p>\n<p>\ufeffDuties and Responsibilities</p>\n<p>\u25cf     To develop and progress the website user interface &amp; optimise applications for maximum speed and scalability.</p>\n<p>\u25cf     Work in an Agile environment to develop the latest and greatest code for web and layout guidance for our Mobile App.</p>\n<p>\u25cf     Code user interface changes to existing features and prototyping and building new features.</p>\n<p>\u25cf     Testing the existing website to ensure that it continually meets internal customer\u2019s expectations.</p>\n<p>\u25cf     Ensure high end user stability and performance using manual and automation testing techniques</p>\n<p>\u25cf     Ensure the technical feasibility of user interface designs and control good quality ux output in line with the overall web and mobile strategy</p>\n<p>\u25cf     Promote and drive best practice</p>\n<p>\u25cf     Stay abreast of latest user interface technology trends</p>\n<p>\u25cf     Provide resource quotations to product owners &amp; business analysts</p>\n<p>\u25cf     Provide accurate information into JIRA</p>\n<p>Skills and Experience Required</p>\n<p>\u25cf     Strong Magento frontend development experience (Magento 1 &amp; 2)</p>\n<p>\u25cf     Strong experience of developing applications using HTML5 / jQuery / Knockout and RequireJs</p>\n<p>\u25cf     Strong experience with CSS3, CSS pre-processors and the differing methodologies (preferred LESS)</p>\n<p>\u25cf     Strong experience of JavaScript</p>\n<p>\u25cf     Strong experience asynchronous control flow, partial page updates, ajax, private Magento content techniques, data layer (Google)</p>\n<p>\u25cf     Strong experience debugging browser behavior &amp; performance issues,</p>\n<p>\u25cf     Can create and operate local development environment using Docker</p>\n<p>\u25cf     Strong Git, GitFlow and Composer skills</p>\n<p>\u25cf     Strong team player</p>\n<p>To Stand Out</p>\n<p>\u25cf     Someone who has skills with Progressive Web App (PWA) development</p>\n<p>\u25cf     Someone who is a JavaScript genius and JavaScript has become your life</p>\n<p>\u25cf     Someone who develops with a \u201cperformance first\u201d mindset</p>\n<p>\u25cf     Someone who can mentor and guide more junior developers</p>\n<p>\u25cf     Someone who loves to learn new technology</p>\n<p>\u25cf     Someone who can talk tech and none tech when neededz</p>\n<p>Eligibility</p>\n<p>\u25cf     You must be eligible to live and work in the UK</p>\n<p>\u25cf     You must be able to work onsite in London (Old Street)</p>\n<p>The Candidate</p>\n<p>Self-motivated, adaptable with a positive attitude\nEnthusiastic and respectful of others\nMust have a \u2018Can do approach\u2019\nFlexible and willing to go the extra mile with a good sense of humour\nMust be able to work autonomously</p>\n<p>Why You\u2019ll Like Working with Us</p>\n<p>You\u2019ll have the opportunity to work on some exciting brands supported by an inspiring and friendly team of people\nYou\u2019ll join a great talented team who are all driven to be the best they can be, while having a lot of fun along the way\nWe offer a place to grow, where you can spread your wings</p>\n',
