      "<p>Quick Take: Axios is a growth-stage startup dedicated to providing trustworthy, award-winning news content in an audience-first format. We are hiring an Infrastructure Engineer!</p>\n<p>Why it Matters: By leveraging your Site Reliability Engineering (SRE) mindset and Infrastructure Engineering expertise, you will play a key role in our mission. You will design, build, and support tools, systems, and workflows that will amplify and enable the efforts of fellow engineers. You will help us optimize our stack and ultimately work toward making our systems faster, more efficient, and able to deal with massive volumes of traffic as we continue to launch worthy products into the world.</p>\n<p>Go Deeper: In this role, you will make an impact on Axios through the following responsibilities:</p>\n<p>Build standards, patterns, and tools that help engineers in other squads make effective use of infrastructure\nConsult with other squads in a SRE capacity to help leverage infrastructure effectively\nConfigure and manage our software defined networking capabilities including VPCs, firewalls, and routing\nAudit and update AWS account and group policies\nConfigure and maintain core shared services like Kubernetes clusters, databases, and CI/CD systems\nBe security-first when designing and evaluating solutions\nHelp audit and harden our production monitoring and alerting systems\nAssist in crafting incident management and release coordination processes\nMentor other team members through pair-programming and empathetic code review\nUnderstand the importance of creating and reviewing documentation</p>\n<p>The Details: A DevOps mindset, the ability to ensure production performance at scale, and a passion for data engineering is the target mix. Ideal candidates will embody a collaborative and entrepreneurial spirit, a passion for Axios\u2019 mission and have the following skills:</p>\n<p>Experience building and maintaining AWS infrastructure\nStrong experience with Kubernetes is preferred\nExperience with CI/CD utilizing CircleCI\nStrong experience with monitoring systems like Prometheus and Grafana\nExperience configuring ingress routing and proxies like Traefik\nExperience writing scripts in a language like Python\nExperience using Terraform\nAn understanding of business continuity and disaster recovery is a plus\u00a0\nProactively seeking to make systems more efficient, faster and cheaper\nFast learner with an ability to work collaboratively</p>\n<p>Don\u2019t forget:</p>\n<p>Competitive salary\nHealth insurance (100% paid for individuals, 75% for families)\nPrimary caregiver 12-week paid leave\n401K\nGenerous vacation policy, plus company holidays\nCompany equity\nCommuter and cell phone benefit\nA commitment to an open, inclusive, and diverse work culture\nAnnual learning and development stipend</p>\n<p>Additional pandemic-related benefits:</p>\n<p>One mental health day per quarter\n$100 monthly work-from-home stipend\nTele-mental health services\u00a0\nOneMedical membership, including tele-health services\u00a0\nIncreased work flexibility for parents and caretakers\u00a0\nAccess to the Axios \u201cFamily Fund\u201d, which was created to allow employees to request financial support when facing financial hardship or emergencies\u00a0\nWeekly company-sponsored exercise and meditation classes\u00a0\nVirtual company-sponsored social events</p>\n",
