      "<p><strong>Engineering Lead (Ruby on Rails)</strong></p>\n<p>We are hiring for an Engineering Lead/Senior Ruby Developer to join our growing organization.</p>\n<p><strong>About us</strong>\nAt OneClickPolitics our mission is to provide innovative and integrated approaches to grassroots advocacy that leverage digital advocacy software tools and technology.</p>\n<p>Hundreds of clients depend on our award-winning advocacy technology, strategic insights, and acquisition services to achieve a measurable impact on policy outcomes at the local, state, provincial, and federal levels of government in the United States, Australia, and Canada.</p>\n<p>Location: OneClickPolitics is headquartered in Washington, DC and this position can be remote or in-office.</p>\n<p><strong>Position</strong></p>\n<p>As Engineering Lead/Senior Ruby Developer, you will be contributing to the development of our code base, managing and expanding our development team, and coordinating ongoing maintenance. This role involves hands-on development as well as leadership for the team\u2019s ongoing development/maintenance of our Ruby on Rails based application. The role will be a hybrid of an Engineering Lead and Senior Ruby Developer and will be integral part of our entire organization reporting to the Board.</p>\n<p><strong>Responsibilities</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Contribute to development of our Ruby on Rails code base and core architecture initiatives</li>\n<li>Lead and grow our team of software engineers through hiring, coaching, mentoring, feedback, and hands-on Ruby on Rails development</li>\n<li>Facilitate collaboration with engineering team, product managers, and designers</li>\n<li>Support timely delivery of technical solutions to address business needs</li>\n<li>Advocate and advance modern, agile engineering practices</li>\n<li>Build a healthy, collaborative engineering culture</li>\n<li>Work remotely with willingness to come into the office for important company collaboration requirements from time to time.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Qualifications</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Minimum 4 years of Ruby on Rails development experience (Front/Backend)</li>\n<li>Minimum 2 years of leadership experience managing development team</li>\n<li>Bachelor\u2019s degree in Computer Science or related field/equivalent experience</li>\n<li>Familiarity with DevOps role and ability to manage team\u2019s DevOps resources</li>\n<li>Experience with managing infrastructure in CI/CD tools</li>\n<li>Experience with infrastructure-as-code methodologies such as Terraform</li>\n<li>Strong background with resource, security, and cost management strategies in AWS implementations</li>\n<li>Natural ability to multitask, prioritize, and manage time efficiently</li>\n</ul>\n<p>You can find all our Openings at\nCareers | OneClickPolitics.</p>\n",
